owing of Old Norse <i>Óláfr</i>."]},{"name":"Calley","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Caley  .","English: variant of the Lancashire name <b>Cayley</b> (see   Caley   2).","Manx: cognate of Scottish Gaelic   Macaulay  , Irish   McAuley  . See also   Cawley   and   Callow  ."]},{"name":"Kailey","meanings":["Manx: variant of   Caley  .","English: variant of <b>Cayley</b>, a habitational name from Cayley in Winwick, Lancashire."]}]},{"name":"Clipsby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Clixby  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Clixby","meanings":["English: locative name from Clixby (Lincs)."]}]},{"name":"Eva","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Popular Latinate form of   Eve  , used also as an Anglicization of the Irish name Aoife ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eva Caley - Clipsby was born in 1371, in Oby, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir William de Cailly, was 27 and her mother, Alice de Braose, was 35. She married Edmund Clipsby. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1394."},"et":{"1371–after 1394":"1371–pärast 1394","1356–Female":"1356–Surnud","1370–1401":"1370–1401","1371–1394":"1371–1394","1371–Male":"1371–Surnud","1372–1417":"1372–1417","1378–Female":"1378–Surnud","1379–1436":"1379–1436","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1383–1454":"1383–1454","1344–1380":"1344–1380","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1383":"1383","1372":"1372","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","Abt 1383":"umbes 1383","1436":"1436","1336":"1336","1379":"1379","1401":"1401","1378":"1378","1356":"1356","1344":"1344","1454":"1454","after 1394":"pärast 1394","1417":"1417","Of, Clipsby, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oby Fleg, Norfolk, Eng.":"Oby, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1371–after 139